# Application code — show, do not auto-edit

**Global project rule. Applies in every session.**

## Default

- **Never** auto-modify `backend/` or `frontend/` unless the user explicitly asks to apply a patch, implement in repo, or similar.
- **Always** return complete, copy-paste-ready code in the response for application work.
- Phrases like **„przygotuj kod”**, **„pokaż implementację”**, **„daj kod”** mean **show code in chat** — NOT write files.

## Auto-edit allowed without extra confirmation

- `docs/` and `ai/` only (documentation, rules, STATUS, decisions).

## Non-trivial tasks (before any application code)

1. Assumptions
2. Plan
3. Impacted files
4. Risks
5. Wait for approval — then **show** code (still no auto-edit unless user says apply/patch/wdróż)

## Explicit permission required to edit application files

User must clearly request one of: patch, diff, wdróż, zastosuj zmiany, zaimplementuj w repozytorium, commit, etc.

## Forbidden

Auto-editing application code when the user only asked to prepare or show code.
